betalain. The effect of model betalains on the lifespan of the wild-type N2 
strain was carefully studied using the automatic platform "Lifespan Machine". In 
a search for different approaches to suppress progeny, pop-1 RNAi was used to 
avoid FUdR use. The presence of betalains in the medium, both as pure compounds 
and as enriched Opuntia extracts significantly increased the lifespan of C. 
elegans.

